        <h1>AMS OVERVIEW</h1>


        <p> I call my desktop application Academic Management System (AMS). I wrote this in VB.NET. This connects to a Microsoft SQL Server database. The master branch is version 1.3.1. The various functionalities of this application are the ability to add application users, teachers, students, and courses into the database, update the entities information, delete the entities, register students with their respective classes, run predefined reports, access control, and look up a student’s grades. This application also implements salting and hashing of passwords behind the scenes. </p>

